Kenya Commercial Bank Says Not Currently in Discussions About Bond Sale

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-04-08T04:26:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/kenya-commercial-bank-says-not-currently-in-discussions-about-bond-sale.html
Kenya Commercial Bank Ltd. (KNCB)  said it’s
currently not involved in any discussions about a planned bond
sale.  Business Daily, a Nairobi-based newspaper, reported today
that the the company plans to sell as much as 8 billion
shillings ($95 million) of debt in the second half of 2011 after
it raised 12.5 billion shillings in a rights issue last year.  Kenya Commercial announced plans in 2009 to raise 20
billion shillings through debt and equity offerings, Kepha
Bosire, spokesman for East African, said in a phone interview
today.  “Last year, we raised capital through equity and we are
not in any discussions for debt because we are well capitalized
at the moment,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  